Vitamin D status and prevalence of metabolic syndrome by race and Hispanic origin in U.S. adults: findings from 2007-2014 NHANES.
Lower Vitamin D status was significantly associated with MetS among U.S. adults after adjusting for sociodemographic and lifestyle factors, dietary supplement use, and BMI. This finding was noted across al race and Hispanic origin groups, although the strength of the association varied being strongest for non-Hispanic White adults.
